<h3 class="date"><a href="/2005/dec/05/">&#x27a0;</a> December 5, 2005</h3>


<div class="row">
    <div class="span12">


    
    <div class="well" id="new_scientist_uk_case_for_hold" >

        
        <a name="002148"></a>
        

        <h4><a class="taggedlink linklink" href="http://www.newscientist.com/article.ns?id=dn8410&amp;feedId=online-news_rss20">New Scientist: UK case for holding terror suspects &#39;misleading&#39;</a></h4>

        

        <p>Politicians&#8217; claims that police need to hold terror suspects for 90 days because of the time taken to decrypt files.  Ross Anderson refutes it, saying &#8220;You find the key lying around, or you give up.&#8221;  Tsk, those pesky experts ruining Tony Blair&#8217;s day.</p>

